.Glue the edges of two mobius strips (twisted piece of paper or anything) and will get a Klein bottle shape thing. Actually that shape won't be close to actual four dimensional Klein bottle.
Informally, it is a one-sided surface which, if traveled upon, could be followed back to the point of origin while flipping the traveler upside down. The Klein bottle can be constructed (in a four dimensional space, because in three dimensional space it cannot be done without allowing the surface to intersect itself) by joining the edges of two Möbius strips together. The Klein bottle was first described in 1882 by the German mathematician Felix Klein. Info source : Numberphile (YouTube) and Wiki
